"{\"abstract\":\"To address the lack of comparative evaluation of Human-in-the-Loop Topic Modeling (HLTM) systems, we implement and evaluate three contrasting HLTM modeling approaches using simulation experiments. These approaches extend previously proposed frameworks, including constraints and informed prior-based methods. Users should have a sense of control in HLTM systems, so we propose a control metric to measure whether refinement operations\\u2019 results match users\\u2019 expectations. Informed prior-based methods provide better control than constraints, but constraints yield higher quality topics.\",\"arxivId\":\"1905.09864\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"40574366\",\"name\":\"Varun Kumar\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/40574366\"},{\"authorId\":\"1405364873\",\"name\":\"Alison Smith-Renner\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1405364873\"},{\"authorId\":\"1689620\",\"name\":\"Leah Findlater\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1689620\"},{\"authorId\":\"31819161\",\"name\":\"K. Seppi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/31819161\"},{\"authorId\":\"1389036863\",\"name\":\"Jordan L. Boyd-Graber\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1389036863\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"81194981\",\"name\":\"A. Smith\"},{\"authorId\":\"40574366\",\"name\":\"Varun Kumar\"},{\"authorId\":\"31819161\",\"name\":\"K. Seppi\"},{\"authorId\":\"1689620\",\"name\":\"Leah Findlater\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1145/3377325.3377491\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"1e35fb78326ef72ff56a9704d84bc2d23656b005\",\"title\":\"Digging into user control: perceptions of adherence and instability in transparent models\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/1e35fb78326ef72ff56a9704d84bc2d23656b005\",\"venue\":\"IUI\",\"year\":2020}],\"corpusId\":165163629,\"doi\":\"10.18653/v1/P19-1637\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitat